text: Both sides of the pew - Democrats and Republicans - have embarrassed themselves. But maybe Congressman Lee Zeldin is the most embarrassing. Maybe we are all doomed.
The only thing more ridiculous is the repetitive comments by both Democrats and Republicans over the last nine hours.

One of the biggest farces is having commentators in the financial media opine on quarterly EPS releases having no more than thirty seconds or so to peruse the headline, based on a casual review of the opening sentence or two of the presser and without any real fincl analysis.
Most solely look at the price reaction. And viewers/listeners actually listen to this nonsense.
Enjoy the evening.
